author: The Wall Street Journal
description:
Costco’s CEO Ron Vachris sat down with The Wall Street Journal to discuss how its $86 billion Kirkland Signature brand runs and why it allows Costco leverage over many big brands. Vachris reveals a Kirkland item he once denied but later approved.

#Costco #Kirkland #Shorts
title: Why Costco's CEO Said 'No' to the Kirkland Signature Bacon-Egg-and-Cheese
